Marlborough Apple Pie
  --Cook's Country
  
4 tbsp unsalted butter
2 granny smith apples, peeled and shredded (2 c)
2 fuji, gala, or golden delicious pples, peeled and shredded (2 c)
1/2 c (3 1/2 oz) sugar
1/4 tsp cinnamon
1/4 ground mace
1/4 tsp salt
3 large eggs, lightly beaten
1/2 c heavy cream
5 tbsp dry sherry
1 tsp grated lemon zest
1 tsp vanilla
9" parpaked pie shell, cooled

Adjust oven rack to lower middle position and heat oven to 325F. Melt butter in 12" skillet over medium heat. Add apples and cook, stirring frequently, until pan is dry and apples have softened, 12-14 min. Transfer apples to bowl and let cool to room temp, ~20 min. Whisk sugar, cinnamon, mace, and salt together in large bowl. Add eggs, cream, sherry, zest, and vanilla and whisk until smooth. Add cooled apples and stir to continue. Pour mixture into pie shell and bake until center is just set, ~40 min. Cool completely on wire rack, ~4 hr. Serve. Can store pie in refrigerator for up to 24 hr.
